description: {"blocks":[{"key":"b93ql","text":"The Amplification and sequencing of HBV pol gene protocol aim to present all the details from HBV DNA extraction with QIAamp DNA Blood Mini Kit (Qiagen, Werfen) and with a homemade assay for amplification/sequencing of the RT region of the HBV pol gene. This protocol is related to an ongoing publication from PLOS ONE.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
keywords: HBV pol gene; HBV sequencing; HBV DNA extraction

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6d2lj","text":"Reagent preparation","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":19}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cf9n8","text":"Protease: Add 5.5 ml of protease solvent included in the kit (nuclease-free water containing 0.04% sodium azide) to the tube containing the lyophilized protease. Reconstituted protease is stable for up to two months when stored at 2-8°C. Storage at -20ºC is recommended to prolong the life of the protease. without residues on top of the plateand invert it.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aec4b","text":"Centrifuge the inverted plate at 150g for 1 minute.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2itcd","text":"Add 150 μl of 70% ethanol, prepared previously, and cover the plate with a new aluminum foil.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"54t93","text":"Centrifuge at 2000g for 5 minutes.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bqqa3","text":"When the centrifugation is finished, remove again the aluminium foil carefully trying to not disturb the sediment.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fig18","text":"Invert the plate over clean towels and centrifuge the inverted plate at 150g for 1 minute.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"86n41","text":"After centrifuging, allow the plate to air dry for approximately 1 minute to eliminate any
 remaining ethanol.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"67kqg","text":"Cover the plate with aluminum foil to store between –15ºC and –25ºC in the dark, but no longer than 2 weeks, or add 20 μl of Hi-DiTM Formamide (Applied Biosystems, USA) and move to the processing phase of the sequences in the ABI Prism 3100-Avant Genetic Analyzer according with the equipment manual.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
